				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've been soloing a lot in Nurga when I wait for a group in BoT/HoH and I always pick the caster mobs first since they don't hurt my pet nearly as much as the melee types.
<br />

<br />
One thing I've noticed which strikes me as odd, not sure if its only them, but if they are doing a "non-damage" detrimental spell like mala-, root, dispell, etc. they will ignore the pet who is always at the top of the hate list and go for me.  With dmg spells (DoTs, nukes) then whoever is at the top of the hate list will get targeted.   The only acception to this is "slow" as they will slow my pet (rarely, maybe 1 in 100 tries will actually land)
<br />

<br />
I just wonder why mobs won't try to mala/root/dispell my pet, and if this is in Nurga only?  
<br />

<br />
This is from months of testing and killing goblins btw.<br />_________________<br />Kimberly Shaw
<br />
