			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am going to take our earth pet as an example.  
<br />

<br />
If it is fighting mulitple mobs, after it succesfully roots a mob, it tries to root a different mob.  
<br />

<br />
I think we are seeing two different effects.   One, if the mobs decides to cast a range spell, it uses it's hate list but ignores distance modifiers.  IE, if we have more hate it ignores the hate bonus of the pet being closer and still casts on us.  
<br />

<br />
If it decides to debuff, it will often debuff {or attempt} to debuff everyone on its hate list before switching spells.  If your pet is the highest on its hate list, it will try to debuff it.  Once it is successful, it will then try to debuff you.  Of course, if you nuke it before it successfully debuffs your pet, it may switch to casting spells on you. 
<br />

<br />
Personally, I have found casters much easier to handle than melee's.  They often get in a casting battle with me and I nuke them down much faster than they take me down.  The most dangerous casters are the ones that cast fear/charm.  MR is good.  I would much pefer they fear/charm me and not my pet.  I generally have good MR and it doesn't not last long.  
<br />

<br />
Just my 2 cp<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449337" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449337</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
