<br />

<br />
When you note that caster mobs give less xp, are you forgetting to tag them?  That is one thing I have nearly forgotten.  Melee mobs need nukes, but Fluffy can beat down a Forsaken Revenant or a Goblin Flamedancer without any help.  Don't forget to dd the mob.
<br />

<br />
I disagree, I think, with Dabrighter2.  You mention that "once successful" at dispelling the pet, he'll move onto you.  In Nurga and Hate, I've NEVER had my pet debuffed a single time.  Not one buff.  However I have had a Spite Golem debuff me with his dying breath.  Now, I'm way off the hate list there because I've done no damage at all.  Can't land a spell.
<br />

<br />
Also, in both places, I have had mobs cast dd spells on me in the middle of a fight, whilst standing and way out of melee range.  Granted the mala or annull line is more common, but I've seen pleanty of Ice Comet effects around my mage (resisted, yay!).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
